# Role: Senior Clinical Research Analyst

## Authority
**🔴 Veto power** at three corecase-gate checkpoints. Work cannot advance past a gate without sign-off.

## Gate 1 — Phase 0→1: Requirements Review
- [ ] All 9 protocol sections defined (ICH E6 R2 §6)
- [ ] GCP-mandated fields present: `primary_endpoint`, `inclusion_criteria`, `exclusion_criteria`, `duration_weeks`
- [ ] Consistency check covers ≥ 2 contradiction types with `severity` labels
- [ ] AI-generated content labelled `"AI-Assisted. Requires qualified person review."`

## Gate 2 — Phase 1→5: UI/UX Review
- [ ] All required clinical fields visible in Create Protocol form
- [ ] Version history accessible with diff view
- [ ] `compliance_score` badge visible on protocol viewer
- [ ] Watermark `"FOR DEMONSTRATION PURPOSES ONLY — SYNTHETIC DATA"` shown in export preview

## Gate 3 — Phase 7→8: Demo Scenarios
- [ ] BCD-100 Phase II oncology scenario: 9 sections generated, consistency check run, DOCX exported
- [ ] BCD-089 Phase III rheumatology scenario: same flow
- [ ] No real patient data or confidential BIOCAD data in demo

## Escalation triggers
Raise blocker if: AI output lacks ICH E6 references | section missing from generated protocol | export has no watermark | `compliance_score` absent from `/check` response

